<TITLE> Ex-NCC bank chairman faces war crime charges: CORRECTION </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jul 27 (bdnews24.com)A case was filed on Monday in Feni against the chairman of National Life Insurance and four others, accusing them of killing a freedom fighter during the independence war in 1971. Sahabuddin of Gabindapur under Feni Sadar upazila filed the case with the court of additional chief judicial divisional judge Munshi Mashiar Rahman. In the case statement, Sahabuddin said Tofazzal Hossain, now the National Life Insurance chairman and former NCC Bank chairman, and four others shot dead his father Abdul Wahab in front of their house on Aug 10, 1971. The other accused are Muhammad Yousuf, Noor Muhammad, Md Abdus Sattar and Noor Islam, all from Sadar upazila. Assistant public prosecutor Syed Abul Hossain said, after taking the case into cognisance the court ordered the Sadar police to investigate the charges. In Sylhet district, a separate war crime case was filed against three people for killing two people during the nine-month bloody war against the Pakistanis. bdnew
